## Additional Terms and Disclaimers

### Educational Purpose
This software is provided for educational and research purposes only. Users are
solely responsible for ensuring their use complies with all applicable laws,
regulations, and terms of service of poker platforms.

### No Affiliation
PokerHUD is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or connected to PokerStars,
Flutter Entertainment, or any other poker platform or company.

### Use at Own Risk
The developers of PokerHUD assume no liability for:
- Account suspensions or bans from poker platforms
- Financial losses incurred while using this software
- Violations of terms of service
- Legal consequences of software usage
- Data loss or corruption

### Passive Monitoring
PokerHUD operates by reading visible screen pixels only (OCR). It does not:
- Read memory from poker client processes
- Intercept network packets
- Modify poker client files
- Inject code into poker applications
- Provide real-time advice or automated decisions

Users must verify that passive screen-reading tools are permitted by their
poker platform's terms of service in their jurisdiction.

### Third-Party Components
This software uses various open-source libraries, each with their own licenses:
- Tesseract OCR (Apache License 2.0)
- PyQt6 (GPL v3 / Commercial License)
- OpenCV (Apache License 2.0)
- And others - see requirements.txt

### Data Privacy
PokerHUD stores player statistics locally on your computer. No data is transmitted
to external servers. Users are responsible for the security and backup of their
local database files.

